{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\sa195\cf1\b\f0\fs20 XMLBlobGet()\cf2  is a generic function that allows you to query whether an element exists, and to fetch it if it does, all in one step. \par
It works for any data type, because the result is returned into a Blob. At that point it is up to you to determine how to handle the data.\par
To use this example, use the\i\f1  Fill XML \i0\f0 and\i\f1  Edit Raw XML\i0\f0  buttons to create and edit the XML file. Then use the Read XML button to bring up a form which allows you to query the XML using \cf1 XMLBlobGet()\cf2 .\par
